sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K648126
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Or tester with cI repressor with very weak RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a test circuit comprised of GFP, mCherry, operating region (Or) of lambda phage, pBAD, and the cI repressor with RBS B0031. When the circuit is induced, the cI repressor is expressed. cI repressor will bind to the binding sites of the operating region. The GFP used is the reverse sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lauren Rossi

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cI lam
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: cI repressor from E. coli phage lambda (+LVA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Elowitz, M. B. Transport, Assembly, and Dynamics in Systems of Interacting Proteins. Thesis, Princeton Univ., Princeton (1999).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for the cI repressor based on cI repressor from bacteriophage lambda modified with an LVA tail for rapid degradation of the protein. cI repressor binds to the cI regulator (BBa_R0051).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
References (unparsed) here:

A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators , Elowitz M.B. , Leibler S., Nature(403),335-38: 2000

Octamerization of CI repressor is needed for effective repression of PRM and efficient switching from lysogeny. Ian B. Dodd,1 Alison J. Perkins, Daniel Tsemitsidis, and J. Barry Egan , Genes and Development (Vol 15, No. 22) 3013-3022: 2001

References (unparsed) here:

A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators , Elowitz M.B. , Leibler S., Nature(403),335-38: 2000

Octamerization of CI repressor is needed for effective repression of PRM and efficient switching from lysogeny. Ian B. Dodd,1 Alison J. Perkins, Daniel Tsemitsidis, and J. Barry Egan , Genes and Development (Vol 15, No. 22) 3013-3022: 2001

BBa_C0051 cI repressor is based on the cI repressor from the Elowitz's repressilator. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LAA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Brian Chow, Peter Carr, Voichita Marinescu and Alexander D. Wissner-Gross

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: green fluorescent protein derived from jellyfish Aequeora victoria wild-type GFP (SwissProt: P42212

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: jcbraff

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0031
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Medium RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-1" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS.

Contact info for this part: Brian Cho
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K648000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RBS B0034 and truncated mCherry with terminator B0015 attached behind it. mCherry was truncated on the N terminus to remove unnecessary methionine codons.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: the n terminus of mCherry had a sequence which could act as a ribosome binding site near an internal methionine codon which could interfere with the the ribosomes affinity for the actual ribosome binding site. The first 8 amino acids were removed without having any effect on fluorescence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lauren Rossi

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K648029
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: OR, operating region for Lambda switch
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The operating region for the Lambda switch that represses C1 and Cro bind to. This region contains promoters prm and pr facing in opposite directions. It also contains operating regions Or3, Or2 and Or1. In the lysogenic state, the C1 dimer is bound naturally bound to the Or1 repressing promotor pr and production of cro. Once RecA cleaves enough C1 dimer the system switches to the lytic state. The Cro produced at the pr promoter then binds to the Or3 site inhibiting the prm promoter. For a better description of the Lambda system read the book "A genetic switch" by Mark Ptashne. We used Or in creation of the lambda system, as part of our project to create a sensor for DNA damage in bacteria due to radiation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: James Coletta, Anisha Katyal, Kristen Salavo, Lauren Rossi

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pBAD
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence was obtained by applying all mutations that upregulated AraC binding and subsequent promoter activity listed in reference [1].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pBAD is an E.coli promoter that is induced by L-arabinose. K206000 is a mutagenized pBAD promoter that is responsive to lower concentrations of arabinose than wild type (I13453) and, additionally, exhibits a higher maximum of protein expression as measured by coupling to a fluorescent reporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There were no special design considerations.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amelia Hardjasa

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mCherry
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: mCherry from Roger Y. Tsien's lab, altered to be BioBrick compatible and with an LVA tag added.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: mRFP (DsRed) derived, altered to be a biobrick by removing a PstI site and adding in the ends.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Made a point mutation to eliminate a PstI site in the middle and then added BioBrick ends with the LVA tag using PCR.

Sequenced using primers that bind to the pSB1A2 plasmid on either side of the brick.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: ytwang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
